  <subsection>
    <title>Notes for <xref ref="sec-dilations-similiarcongruent"/></title>
  <p>
    <xref ref="explore-scalefactor-proportion"/> can be done virtually or on 
      paper copies. The grid allows students to make computations that are more 
      precise than a ruler. Besides being a review, the first task emphasizes that 
      the scale factor is equal to the constant of proportionality and that
      <m>\frac{AA'}{OA'}</m> is a different value. In fact, in this example,
        <md>
          <mrow> \frac{AA'}{OA'}\amp =\frac{OA'-OA}{OA'} </mrow>
          <mrow> \amp =\frac{OA'}{OA'}-\frac{OA}{OA'}</mrow>
          <mrow> \amp =1-\frac{1}{k}</mrow>
        </md>
      where <m>k</m> is the scale factor.
  </p>
